[
  {
    "text": "Linking your app against the iOS 11 SDK ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=1"
  },
  {
    "text": "is the only thing you need to do in order to take advantage ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=3"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the super Retina display on iPhone X. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=6"
  },
  {
    "text": "If your app is largely based on standard UIKit controls ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "and you use Auto Layout, then you're in good shape ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=12"
  },
  {
    "text": "since most of the work will be done for you by UIKit.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=15"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you use custom controls, or you're not using Auto Layout, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=19"
  },
  {
    "text": "or if you're a custom full screen app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=23"
  },
  {
    "text": "like many games are, don't worry. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=25"
  },
  {
    "text": "While there may be some work for you to do, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=27"
  },
  {
    "text": "it's not difficult and there is lots of support built in ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=29"
  },
  {
    "text": "with tools like the new Safe Area layout guides. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=32"
  },
  {
    "text": "In either case, you will want to thoroughly test your app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=35"
  },
  {
    "text": "especially in landscape, to make sure everything looks right.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=38"
  },
  {
    "text": "The latest version of Xcode includes simulator support ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=43"
  },
  {
    "text": "for iPhone X, allowing you to make most layout changes, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=45"
  },
  {
    "text": "especially any adjustments ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=49"
  },
  {
    "text": "relating to respecting the Safe Area. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=51"
  },
  {
    "text": "For some apps, like ones that use Metal, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=54"
  },
  {
    "text": "or hardware features like the front-facing camera, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=56"
  },
  {
    "text": "you may need to use an actual device. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=59"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's take a quick look at the new iPhone X simulator. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=62"
  },
  {
    "text": "Just like other iPhone or iPad simulators, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=65"
  },
  {
    "text": "you'll have access to many of the built-in system apps. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=68"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is a great way to see examples ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=71"
  },
  {
    "text": "of how different UIKit components behave on iPhone X. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=73"
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, the Files app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "shows many of the latest iOS 11 APIs in action, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=79"
  },
  {
    "text": "like the integrated search bar or large navigation bar titles. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=83"
  },
  {
    "text": "And don't forget, you can sign into your iCloud account ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=87"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the simulator, which gives you access to iCloud Drive. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=90"
  },
  {
    "text": "This makes it really easy to transfer files ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=94"
  },
  {
    "text": "or test content like photos into the simulator. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=96"
  },
  {
    "text": "Another good example is the Contacts app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=100"
  },
  {
    "text": "which shows how table views behave on iPhone X. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=103"
  },
  {
    "text": "Be sure to rotate the simulator to landscape ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=107"
  },
  {
    "text": "where you can see behaviors like the section headers ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=109"
  },
  {
    "text": "going edge to edge, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=111"
  },
  {
    "text": "but the table contents remain indented ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=113"
  },
  {
    "text": "according to the Safe Area. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=115"
  },
  {
    "text": "We'll talk more about table views a bit later. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=118"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's move on to an app that I work on, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=121"
  },
  {
    "text": "the WWDC app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=123"
  },
  {
    "text": "I've spent a little time moving it over to iPhone X ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=125"
  },
  {
    "text": "and I'd like to share some layout issues ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=128"
  },
  {
    "text": "that I encountered, and how I fixed them. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=130"
  },
  {
    "text": "The WWDC app is actually a pretty typical real-world app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=132"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's been around for a number of years ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=136"
  },
  {
    "text": "and it's been worked on by various engineers ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=139"
  },
  {
    "text": "from year to year. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=140"
  },
  {
    "text": "While it uses lots of standard controls and Auto Layout, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "it also has custom views, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=145"
  },
  {
    "text": "and older parts of the app do manual layout instead. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=147"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll use it to highlight three different areas ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=150"
  },
  {
    "text": "that needed to be updated for iPhone X. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=152"
  },
  {
    "text": "I've started by opening the project in Xcode 9 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=156"
  },
  {
    "text": "and set the Base SDK to iOS 11. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=158"
  },
  {
    "text": "So we're all set to run at the native resolution. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=161"
  },
  {
    "text": "When you do this with your app, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=164"
  },
  {
    "text": "if you don't see it running at the full iPhone X resolution, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=166"
  },
  {
    "text": "double check that you've configured a Launch Storyboard, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=170"
  },
  {
    "text": "as that's also needed. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=172"
  },
  {
    "text": "OK, our initial view is the Videos tab, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=175"
  },
  {
    "text": "and this looks pretty good. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=177"
  },
  {
    "text": "This was all new code this year ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=179"
  },
  {
    "text": "using UICollectionView with Auto Layout, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=181"
  },
  {
    "text": "along with standard navigation bar and toolbar controls. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=183"
  },
  {
    "text": "So I'm not really surprised that most of the interface ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=187"
  },
  {
    "text": "lays out correctly, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=189"
  },
  {
    "text": "because UIKit is doing most of the work for me. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=190"
  },
  {
    "text": "One place where we don't use Auto Layout ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=194"
  },
  {
    "text": "is on the News tab. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=196"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's have a look at that. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=197"
  },
  {
    "text": "This view actually looks pretty good, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=199"
  },
  {
    "text": "even though it's doing manual layout of the UI. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=201"
  },
  {
    "text": "While we're not using Auto Layout directly, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=204"
  },
  {
    "text": "the code doing the layout is paying attention ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=207"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the layout margin insets, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=209"
  },
  {
    "text": "and UIKit is automatically adjusting those ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=211"
  },
  {
    "text": "to respect the Safe Area. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=214"
  },
  {
    "text": "The first problem that I encountered ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=216"
  },
  {
    "text": "is here on the News tab, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=218"
  },
  {
    "text": "and it's in the fullscreen photo viewer. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=219"
  },
  {
    "text": "Even though this particular view uses Auto Layout, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=223"
  },
  {
    "text": "the page control is too far down at the bottom of the screen. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=226"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's running into the Home indicator. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=229"
  },
  {
    "text": "The problem here is that the page control's bottom constraint ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=233"
  },
  {
    "text": "is relative to the superview, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=236"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is full screen and goes behind the Home indicator. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=238"
  },
  {
    "text": "Instead of constraining to the superview, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=243"
  },
  {
    "text": "what we should do is constrain the page control ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=245"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the Safe Area layout guide at the bottom. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=247"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's make that change now.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=250"
  },
  {
    "text": "I've opened this interface in Xcode, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=254"
  },
  {
    "text": "but before I can adjust the constraint ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=256"
  },
  {
    "text": "I need to enable Safe Area layout guides in this xib file. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=258"
  },
  {
    "text": "Storyboards and xibs created prior to Xcode 9 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=262"
  },
  {
    "text": "will not automatically have ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=266"
  },
  {
    "text": "Safe Area layout guides turned on. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=267"
  },
  {
    "text": "Go to the Document inspector ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=271"
  },
  {
    "text": "and select the Use Safe Area Layout Guides checkbox. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=272"
  },
  {
    "text": "One thing to note here is that for iOS storyboards, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=278"
  },
  {
    "text": "turning this on will automatically upgrade ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=281"
  },
  {
    "text": "constraints tied to the scene's top and bottom layout guides, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=283"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as leading and trailing edges. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=287"
  },
  {
    "text": "So be sure to review and test your Auto Layout constraints ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=290"
  },
  {
    "text": "after turning this on.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=293"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now I can select the bottom constraint of the page control. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=296"
  },
  {
    "text": "And look at the Attributes inspector for this constraint. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=300"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here we see that the constraint is connected ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=304"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the superview's bottom edge ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=305"
  },
  {
    "text": "and that's what is keeping the control too far down. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=308"
  },
  {
    "text": "Instead of the Superview, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=311"
  },
  {
    "text": "if we change this to be connected to the Safe Area, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=313"
  },
  {
    "text": "then on iPhone X the page indicator ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=316"
  },
  {
    "text": "will automatically move up above the Home indicator.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=318"
  },
  {
    "text": "When I build and run now, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=322"
  },
  {
    "text": "the page control is at the right place, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=324"
  },
  {
    "text": "and this works for both portrait and landscape. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=326"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's move on to the second issue that I found, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=330"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is over in the Videos tab. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=333"
  },
  {
    "text": "Once again, things look pretty good, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=335"
  },
  {
    "text": "but if I bring up the search field, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=337"
  },
  {
    "text": "well, that doesn't look quite right. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=340"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's compare this to the Contacts app looks. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=342"
  },
  {
    "text": "A couple things look wrong here. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=345"
  },
  {
    "text": "The color of the search bar background isn't quite right, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=347"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the sizing is a bit off. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=349"
  },
  {
    "text": "And if I rotate to landscape, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=352"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can see things don't look right here either. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=354"
  },
  {
    "text": "The search field and Cancel buttons are both being clipped ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=356"
  },
  {
    "text": "by the rounded corners of the screen. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=359"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is a typical example where paying attention ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=361"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the Safe Area is really important. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=363"
  },
  {
    "text": "For this search field, what the WWDC app is doing ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=367"
  },
  {
    "text": "is explicitly presenting a UI search controller. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=370"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now in iOS 11, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=374"
  },
  {
    "text": "the search bar can be integrated with the navigation bar, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=376"
  },
  {
    "text": "which will give the right presentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=379"
  },
  {
    "text": "like we saw in Contacts. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=380"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's look at the code and make that change.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=383"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's the code that presents our search controller. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=386"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm going to make two changes. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=389"
  },
  {
    "text": "First, instead of presenting the search controller, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=390"
  },
  {
    "text": "we'll hand it to the UINavigationItem ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=393"
  },
  {
    "text": "for this view controller. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=395"
  },
  {
    "text": "And second, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=397"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll set the search controller's isActive property to true. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=399"
  },
  {
    "text": "This will cause the navigation bar ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=403"
  },
  {
    "text": "to activate it and start editing. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=404"
  },
  {
    "text": "Notice that we can use the availability support ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=407"
  },
  {
    "text": "to only do this for iOS 11, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=409"
  },
  {
    "text": "while preserving the existing behavior ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=412"
  },
  {
    "text": "for older versions of iOS. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=413"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's build and run to see how that looks. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=416"
  },
  {
    "text": "Much better. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=418"
  },
  {
    "text": "This looks like the correct presentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=419"
  },
  {
    "text": "of the search field for iOS 11. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=421"
  },
  {
    "text": "And in landscape? Terrific. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=423"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now the search bar is fitting into the Safe Area nicely, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=426"
  },
  {
    "text": "and this is all being automatically managed for us ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=429"
  },
  {
    "text": "by the navigation bar. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=432"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you have search bars in your UI with navigation bars, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=434"
  },
  {
    "text": "you definitely want to make a similar change on iOS 11.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=437"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now let's take a look at the third part of the app ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=442"
  },
  {
    "text": "that I needed to work on. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=444"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here in the Schedule tab, we are using a UITableView. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=446"
  },
  {
    "text": "The layout in portrait looks pretty good, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=450"
  },
  {
    "text": "although we've got another case of a search bar ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=452"
  },
  {
    "text": "that doesn't look right. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=454"
  },
  {
    "text": "This one happens to be getting inserted ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=456"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the table view as a header view, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=458"
  },
  {
    "text": "but we can apply the same change as before ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=460"
  },
  {
    "text": "to integrate it with the navigation bar instead. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=462"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll set the search controller ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=465"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the view controller's navigation item, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=467"
  },
  {
    "text": "and set the active state appropriately. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=469"
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's build and run. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=472"
  },
  {
    "text": "This looks great. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=473"
  },
  {
    "text": "If I rotate to landscape, the search field looks fine ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=475"
  },
  {
    "text": "and most of the UI looks like it's respecting the safe areas. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=478"
  },
  {
    "text": "But if you look closely, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=482"
  },
  {
    "text": "we use a custom background color ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=484"
  },
  {
    "text": "for the table section header, and that looks wrong. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=486"
  },
  {
    "text": "The color should be extending to the edge of the screen, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=490"
  },
  {
    "text": "like they do in the Contacts app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=493"
  },
  {
    "text": "If we look at the code, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=495"
  },
  {
    "text": "we can see that the app is setting the background color ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=498"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the contentView of the header view. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=500"
  },
  {
    "text": "That seems like a reasonable thing to do, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=503"
  },
  {
    "text": "and in fact, it works fine on iPhones other than iPhone X. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=505"
  },
  {
    "text": "So what is the problem here? ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=510"
  },
  {
    "text": "To understand what's happening, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=512"
  },
  {
    "text": "we need to look at the details of how a table view ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=514"
  },
  {
    "text": "lays things out on iPhone X. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=516"
  },
  {
    "text": "To help illustrate this, let's start with the really useful ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=519"
  },
  {
    "text": "View Hierarchy Debugger in Xcode. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=522"
  },
  {
    "text": "Here's that view we were looking at. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=525"
  },
  {
    "text": "Down in the bottom right, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=528"
  },
  {
    "text": "I can adjust the visible view range ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=529"
  },
  {
    "text": "to hide all the views except the table view itself. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=531"
  },
  {
    "text": "The table view will be the full size of the screen. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=536"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now I'll adjust the visible range ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=539"
  },
  {
    "text": "to include the cells of the table view. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=541"
  },
  {
    "text": "Notice how the cells extend from edge to edge. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=544"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll select one to highlight it, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=547"
  },
  {
    "text": "and overlay the Safe Area on top of this view ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=550"
  },
  {
    "text": "to illustrate where it would be. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=553"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now I'll keep extending the visible range ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=556"
  },
  {
    "text": "to pull more views into the picture.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=558"
  },
  {
    "text": "What we're seeing now is that the content view of the cells ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=562"
  },
  {
    "text": "have been automatically inset to the Safe Area. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=565"
  },
  {
    "text": "So this causes a discrepancy ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=568"
  },
  {
    "text": "between the size of the table cell, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=570"
  },
  {
    "text": "the one that goes from edge to edge, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=572"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the content view of the cell, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=575"
  },
  {
    "text": "which has been inset.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=577"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'll highlight a few of the views ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=579"
  },
  {
    "text": "that are involved here. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=581"
  },
  {
    "text": "But now this picture is getting a bit busy, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=583"
  },
  {
    "text": "so let's simplify this and label these views.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=585"
  },
  {
    "text": "By default, table cells will inset their content views ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=589"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that they are inside the Safe Area. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=593"
  },
  {
    "text": "That insetting behavior is something that you can control. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=595"
  },
  {
    "text": "In Xcode, you can use ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=599"
  },
  {
    "text": "the Content View Insets to Safe Area checkbox. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=601"
  },
  {
    "text": "There's a corresponding property you can set in code as well.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=605"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you uncheck the checkbox, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=609"
  },
  {
    "text": "then the content view will not be inset, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=611"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the content view will now go from edge to edge.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=615"
  },
  {
    "text": "One final point here ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=619"
  },
  {
    "text": "is that regardless of the content view's insetting, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=621"
  },
  {
    "text": "the layout margins in the content view ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=624"
  },
  {
    "text": "will continue to be relative to the Safe Area by default. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=626"
  },
  {
    "text": "Similar to the content view insetting, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=630"
  },
  {
    "text": "there are properties that give you control ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=633"
  },
  {
    "text": "over the behavior of these layout margins. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=635"
  },
  {
    "text": "You can get more details about this ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=638"
  },
  {
    "text": "and other margin-related options in the documentation ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=639"
  },
  {
    "text": "and WWDC videos which I'll mention at the end.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=643"
  },
  {
    "text": "OK, now that we've seen how table views position their cells ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=647"
  },
  {
    "text": "with regard to the Safe Area, let's go back to the code ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=651"
  },
  {
    "text": "where we were setting the background color ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=653"
  },
  {
    "text": "on the header view. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=655"
  },
  {
    "text": "We can see that we're setting it only on the content view, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=657"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is being inset to the Safe Area.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=660"
  },
  {
    "text": "At this point, there are a couple different ways ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=664"
  },
  {
    "text": "we could fix this problem. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=666"
  },
  {
    "text": "One of them would be ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=668"
  },
  {
    "text": "to disable the table view's default behavior ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=669"
  },
  {
    "text": "of insetting content views to the Safe Area, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=671"
  },
  {
    "text": "but doing that will affect everything else ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=675"
  },
  {
    "text": "in our content view as well, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=677"
  },
  {
    "text": "and we'd lose this helpful default behavior. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=679"
  },
  {
    "text": "Instead, the best solution here ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=681"
  },
  {
    "text": "is to set the background color of the background view, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=683"
  },
  {
    "text": "which, unlike the inset content view, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=687"
  },
  {
    "text": "spans the full width of the cell ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=690"
  },
  {
    "text": "regardless of any Safe Area insets.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=692"
  },
  {
    "text": "With that change, when we build and run, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=696"
  },
  {
    "text": "we go from this, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=699"
  },
  {
    "text": "where the header background color doesn't go edge to edge, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=701"
  },
  {
    "text": "to this, where the colors span the entire table ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=705"
  },
  {
    "text": "but the content view isn't changed at all. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=708"
  },
  {
    "text": "That looks much better.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=711"
  },
  {
    "text": "Those are three examples of issues I encountered ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=715"
  },
  {
    "text": "while updating the WWDC app for iPhone X. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=717"
  },
  {
    "text": "They weren't difficult to fix, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=721"
  },
  {
    "text": "and mostly had to do with landscape view. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=723"
  },
  {
    "text": "A few quick reminders. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=726"
  },
  {
    "text": "Linking against the iOS 11 SDK ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=728"
  },
  {
    "text": "and including a Launch Storyboard ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=730"
  },
  {
    "text": "will enable the fullscreen native resolution for your app. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=732"
  },
  {
    "text": "And while you may see some issues in portrait, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=736"
  },
  {
    "text": "the majority will very likely be in landscape ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=738"
  },
  {
    "text": "so be sure to test all your UI with the interface rotated, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=740"
  },
  {
    "text": "both to the left and to the right. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=744"
  },
  {
    "text": "You'll avoid most issues by respecting the Safe Areas. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=747"
  },
  {
    "text": "Auto Layout and the safeAreaLayoutGuides ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=750"
  },
  {
    "text": "will handle a lot of the layout challenges automatically, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=753"
  },
  {
    "text": "but if you're doing manual layout ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=756"
  },
  {
    "text": "you do have access to the Safe Area insets ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=758"
  },
  {
    "text": "and can do whatever calculations you need. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=761"
  },
  {
    "text": "This information is available via the UIView class. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=764"
  },
  {
    "text": "It's also important to not interfere with ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=768"
  },
  {
    "text": "the Home indicator at the bottom of the screen. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=770"
  },
  {
    "text": "For details about the Home indicator ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=773"
  },
  {
    "text": "and many of the other aspects of designing for iPhone X, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=775"
  },
  {
    "text": "be sure to watch the Designing for iPhone X video ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=779"
  },
  {
    "text": "which has lots of important details ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=782"
  },
  {
    "text": "for bringing your app to this new screen. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=783"
  },
  {
    "text": "There were also a few key videos at WWDC 2017 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-201/?time=786"
